.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`write_table\*(C'\fR gives better warnings for incorrect types of data given
.PP
Numerous changes to dist.ini to improve \s-1CPAN\s0 testing, especially for Win32
.SS "0.12"
.IX Subsection "0.12"
\&\f(CW\*(C`add_data\*(C'\fR can also take hash of arrays, and various mixes of data types
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`ljoin\*(C'\fR: Addition of \f(CW\*(C`restrict\*(C'\fR keywords in many places; should improve \s-1CPU\s0 performance
.PP
Better \s-1POD\s0 formatting, correction of output hash for \s-1README\s0's \f(CW\*(C`add_data\*(C'\fR
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`chisq_test\*(C'\fR can now accept hash of hashes as input
.PP
new \f(CW\*(C`transpose\*(C'\fR function for switching 2D hash keys and 2D array indices, and \f(CW\*(C`col2col\*(C'\fR for comparing columns against columns
.PP
removed unused function from C helpers
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`value_counts\*(C'\fR: addition of restrict keywords in preinit, should improve \s-1CPU\s0 performance
.PP
\&\s-1MANIFEST\s0.skip changed to \s-1MANIFEST\s0.SKIP to improve \s-1CPAN\s0 testing
.PP
using \f(CW\*(C`is_deeply\*(C'\fR for tests of \f(CW\*(C`transpose\*(C'\fR, which may or may not work with \s-1CPAN\s0 testers (experimental)
.PP
Added function name to warnings, so I actually know which function is producing the error
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`write_table\*(C'\fR can also take \f(CW\*(C`file\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`data\*(C'\fR as args, in addition to positions
.PP
fixed \f(CW\*(C`write_table\*(C'\fR as it could hang if given empty \f(CW\*(C`col.names\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`row.names\*(C'\fR
.PP
Added \f(CW\*(C`_\|_EXTENSIONS_\|_\*(C'\fR to source \s-1XS\s0 file for better \s-1CPAN\s0 testing
.SS "0.11"
.IX Subsection "0.11"
better \s-1POD\s0 formatting for tables
.PP
addition of \s-1MANIFEST\s0.skip to get better testing results on \s-1CPAN\s0
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`glm\*(C'\fR: bugfix for when there is no intercept in the formula, new test cases in t/glm.t
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`write_table\*(C'\fR now accepts simple hashes as input, in addition to hash of arrays, hash of hashes, and arrays of hashes
.PP
Better documentation for t\-test
.SS "0.10"
.IX Subsection "0.10"
changes to compilation for \s-1CPAN\s0, trying to get this work on Windows
.PP
Addition of \f(CW\*(C`prcomp\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`value_counts\*(C'\fR
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`matrix\*(C'\fR will work without key names, just like in R.  Testing for \f(CW\*(C`matrix\*(C'\fR has improved.
.SS "0.09"
.IX Subsection "0.09"
context changes in \s-1XS\s0 \f(CW\*(C`dTHX\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`pTHX_\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`aTHX_\*(C'\fR to get better \s-1CPAN\s0 testing results
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`restrict\*(C'\fR keywords added to \f(CW\*(C`lm\*(C'\fR to increase speed
.SS "0.08"
.IX Subsection "0.08"
Speed improvement in \f(CW\*(C`summary\*(C'\fR of hashes.
.PP
Addition of \f(CW\*(C`add_data\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`dnorm\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`group_by\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`ljoin\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`mode\*(C'\fR functions
.PP
Chi-squared function no longer has Perl wrapper, and all code is in \s-1XS\s0, which should result in a minor speed increase with 1 less function call.
.PP
Compiler changes for \s-1GNU\s0 source and inclusion of \f(CW\*(C`strings.h\*(C'\fR, to ensure more \s-1CPAN\s0 testing works better.
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`read_table\*(C'\fR now returns hash-of-hash in {row}{column}
.SS "0.07"
.IX Subsection "0.07"
Addition of \f(CW\*(C`summary\*(C'\fR function.
.PP
Formulas can now be omitted from \f(CW\*(C`aov\*(C'\fR, resulting in a stacked calculation as R would think.
.PP
Addition of \f(CW\*(C`oneway_test\*(C'\fR for multi-group comparisons that does not assume normality like \f(CW\*(C`aov\*(C'\fR does.
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`read_table\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`write_table\*(C'\fR now automatically set separators for \f(CW\*(C`.csv\*(C'\fR files as \f(CW\*(C`,\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`.tsv\*(C'\fR files as \f(CW"\et"\fR, respectively, so these values no longer need to be specified separately from the file name.
.SS "0.06"
.IX Subsection "0.06"
Changed compiler options so that Solaris will work
.PP
signed integers changed to unsigned in \f(CW\*(C`glm\*(C'\fR
.PP
Added restrict keywords to \f(CW\*(C`power_t_test\*(C'\fR, and made \f(CW\*(C`int\*(C'\fR to \f(CW\*(C`unsigned int\*(C'\fR
.SS "0.05"
.IX Subsection "0.05"
Leak testing for \f(CW\*(C`sample\*(C'\fR
.PP
removal of Data::Printer dependency for easier \s-1CPAN\s0 testing
.PP
switched several \f(CW\*(C`unsigned int\*(C'\fR variable to \f(CW\*(C`I32\*(C'\fR so that clang doesn't complain
.PP
added restrict keyword for \f(CW\*(C`sample\*(C'\fR
.SS "0.04"
.IX Subsection "0.04"
addition of \f(CW\*(C`sample\*(C'\fR function
.PP
\&\s-1GNU\s0 source, to maximize compatibility and ease installation
.PP
removal of \s-1JSON\s0 dependency to ease installation
.SS "0.03"
.IX Subsection "0.03"
Compatibility back to Perl 5.10
.SS "0.02"
.IX Subsection "0.02"
back-compatible to Perl 5.10, instead of original 5.40, ensuring more people can use it
.PP
added var_test
.PP
mean, min, sum, median, var, and max die with undefined values, and print the offending indices
.PP
\&\*(L"group_stats\*(R" added to aov, for TukeyHSD in the future
.PP
\&\*(L"cor\*(R" dies when given data with standard deviation of 0
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`write_table\*(C'\fR now has \f(CW\*(C`undef.val\*(C'\fR option, which shows how undefined values are printed to tables, which is \f(CW\*(C`NA\*(C'\fR by default.
